      "story_title": "I got in an accident when I was away at college and lost my right eye. I never told my parents and they still don’t know I have a glass eye…it’s been 7 years",
      "story_url": "https://reddit.com/r/confession/comments/1r4bh7n/i_got_in_an_accident_when_i_was_away_at_college/",
      "story": "Back in college, I was blackout drunk and on Xanax at a party. I somehow managed to shoot myself point-blank in the eye with a high-powered airsoft gun. Yeah, I know. It was a complete freak accident, but my eye was so mangled it had to be completely removed. I never told my parents because I didn't want them to find out about the drugs. My rich girlfriend's millionaire dad stepped in, paid for my surgery, and got me the most incredibly realistic prosthetic eye, all while keeping it a secret from my family. I figured my parents would notice instantly when I came home, but nope. Seven years later, they still have no idea. Honestly, this thing is a work of art, so realistic you'd never guess. It's not just them either; nobody from my hometown knows. I'm finally ready to tell everyone, but I want to do a big, funny reveal. Any suggestions, Reddit?",
